<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>BoxLang Charts Module - Test Suite</title>
	<bx:include template="includes/head.bxm">
</head>
<body>
	<div class="container">
		<header>
			<h1>📊 BoxLang Charts Module</h1>
			<div class="subtitle">Interactive Chart.js Integration Test Suite</div>
			<div class="version">v1.0.0</div>
		</header>

		<div class="intro">
			<h2>Welcome to the BoxLang Charts Test Suite</h2>
			<p>
				This test suite demonstrates the comprehensive charting capabilities of the BoxLang Charts module.
				Built on the powerful Chart.js library, this module brings beautiful, interactive data visualizations
				to your BoxLang applications with minimal code.
			</p>

			<div class="highlight">
				<strong>🎯 10 Chart Types Supported:</strong> pie, bar, line, doughnut, radar, polarArea, area, horizontalbar, scatter, bubble
			</div>

			<div class="features">
				<div class="feature">
					<h3>🎨 Styling</h3>
					<ul>
						<li>Custom colors</li>
						<li>Font customization</li>
						<li>Legends & titles</li>
						<li>Background colors</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="feature">
					<h3>📏 Layout</h3>
					<ul>
						<li>Responsive design</li>
						<li>Custom dimensions</li>
						<li>Aspect ratios</li>
						<li>Grid lines</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="feature">
					<h3>⚙️ Advanced</h3>
					<ul>
						<li>Stacked/clustered series</li>
						<li>Axis titles</li>
						<li>Multiple series</li>
						<li>Data labels</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="feature">
					<h3>🚀 Performance</h3>
					<ul>
						<li>Fast rendering</li>
						<li>Canvas-based</li>
						<li>Optimized assets</li>
						<li>Production ready</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<h2>
			📋 Test Examples
		</h2>

		<div class="test-links">
			<a href="charts.bxm" class="test-card">
				<h2>🎯 Comprehensive Examples</h2>
				<p>
					A complete showcase of all 10 supported chart types with various styling options,
					axis configurations, and layout features. Perfect for learning the basics and
					exploring different chart options.
				</p>
				<div class="chart-types">
					<span class="chart-type">Pie</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Bar</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Line</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Doughnut</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Radar</span>
					<span class="chart-type">PolarArea</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Area</span>
					<span class="chart-type">HorizontalBar</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Scatter</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Bubble</span>
				</div>
				<span class="btn">View Examples →</span>
			</a>

			<a href="charts-enhanced.bxm" class="test-card">
				<h2>✨ Enhanced Features</h2>
				<p>
					Advanced chart configurations showcasing enhanced features like stacked series,
					custom axis titles, grid line controls, and font styling. Demonstrates the
					full power of the charting module.
				</p>
				<div class="chart-types">
					<span class="chart-type">Axis Titles</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Grid Lines</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Stacked Series</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Font Styling</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Custom Colors</span>
				</div>
				<span class="btn">View Enhanced →</span>
			</a>

			<a href="charts-responsive.bxm" class="test-card">
				<h2>📱 Responsive Features</h2>
				<p>
					Interactive demonstrations of responsive chart behavior with different aspect ratios,
					container sizes, and mobile-friendly configurations. Resize your browser to see
					charts adapt in real-time.
				</p>
				<div class="chart-types">
					<span class="chart-type">Responsive</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Aspect Ratios</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Mobile-Ready</span>
					<span class="chart-type">Container Sizing</span>
				</div>
				<span class="btn">View Responsive →</span>
			</a>
		</div>
		<bx:include template="includes/footer.bxm">
	</div>
</body>
</html>
